U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer
 George Osborne  said the government will cut the top rate of
income tax to 45 percent from 50 percent from April next year.  Osborne made the comments to lawmakers in Parliament in
 London  today as he presented his annual budget.  To contact the reporter on this story:
